   287	### D. Bare-repo bootstrap â€” one authoritative owner
   288	
   289	**Owner:** `setup-experiment.sh`. The repo is seeded **before**
   290	`docker compose up` runs, so the seed SHA is known synchronously and
   291	can be written into `.env` for downstream service flags.
   292	
   293	**Mechanism:** setup-experiment runs a one-shot
   294	
   295	```bash
   296	docker compose --env-file <generated-env> run --rm eden-repo-init
   297	```
   298	
   299	against a new `eden-repo-init` service in `compose.yaml`. That
   300	service:
   301	
   302	1. `image:` references the same shared `eden-reference:dev` image
   303	   (so it has Python + the workspace + git available).
   304	2. Mounts only the `eden-bare-repo` named volume at
   305	   `/var/lib/eden/repo`.
   306	3. `command: ["python", "-m", "eden_service_common.repo_init",
   307	   "--repo-path", "/var/lib/eden/repo"]` â€” a new module that:
   308	   a. If `/var/lib/eden/repo/HEAD` already exists, prints
   309	      `EDEN_REPO_ALREADY_SEEDED sha=<existing-sha>` and exits 0.
   310	   b. Otherwise: runs `git init --bare
   311	      --initial-branch=main`, calls `seed_bare_repo`, prints
   312	      `EDEN_REPO_SEEDED sha=<hex>` to stdout, exits 0.
   313	
   314	The script captures stdout, parses the SHA, and writes it to `.env`
   315	as `EDEN_BASE_COMMIT_SHA=<hex>`. Then the operator runs `docker
   316	compose up`.
   317	
   318	**Crucially:** `eden-repo-init` is **NOT** in any other service's
   319	`depends_on`. It is a setup-time tool, invoked by setup-experiment
   320	via `compose run --rm`, not a `compose up`-time dependency. This
   321	collapses the dual-owner contradiction codex flagged in plan-review
   322	round 0: setup-experiment is the sole owner of repo seeding, and
   323	the seed SHA is known *before* any service starts.
   324	
   325	The compose `profiles:` keyword keeps `eden-repo-init` out of plain
   326	`docker compose up`'s service set:
   327	
   328	```yaml
   329	eden-repo-init:
   330	  profiles: ["setup"]
   331	  ...
   332	```
   333	
   334	`compose run --rm <name>` runs services regardless of profile, so
   335	setup-experiment invokes it normally; plain `compose up` skips it.
   336	
   337	**Re-runnability:** `setup-experiment.sh` is idempotent. Running it
   338	a second time:
   339	
   340	- Re-runs `eden-repo-init`, which short-circuits on the existing
   341	  `HEAD` and re-prints the existing SHA.
   342	- Preserves existing secrets (postgres password, shared token) so
   343	  re-running doesn't rotate them by accident.
   344	- Overwrites `EDEN_PLAN_TASKS` and `experiment-config.yaml`.
   345	
   346	### E. setup-experiment script
   347	
   348	**File:** [`reference/scripts/setup-experiment/setup-experiment.sh`](../../reference/scripts/setup-experiment/setup-experiment.sh)
   349	(plus `README.md`).
   350	
   351	**Why bash, not Python:** the script's job is mostly to (a) read a
   352	YAML field from an existing config, (b) generate a `.env` file from
   353	a template, (c) print human-readable next steps. Bash is the
   354	simplest tool that fits, and it doesn't introduce a "you must `uv
   355	sync` before you can set up an experiment" bootstrap problem.
   356	Python would make the YAML read prettier (vs. `yq` or `python3 -c
   357	"import yaml; â€¦"`), but trades it for the bootstrap requirement.
   358	The bash script will use a one-line `python3 -c` for YAML parsing
   359	since CI's runner has Python â€” that single dependency stays minor.
   360	
   361	**Inputs:**
   362	
   363	- Required positional arg: path to an experiment config YAML
   364	  (defaults to repo's fixture at
   365	  `tests/fixtures/experiment/.eden/config.yaml`).
   366	- `--experiment-id <id>` (default: derived from config filename
   367	  parent directory).
   368	- `--shared-token <T>` (default: a freshly generated 32-byte hex
   369	  string).
   370	- `--postgres-password <P>` (default: read from existing `.env` if
   371	  present, else freshly generated).
   372	
   373	**Outputs:**
   374	
   375	- `reference/compose/.env` (or `--env-file <path>`) â€” generated
   376	  Compose env. See section F for the full variable list.
   377	- `reference/compose/experiment-config.yaml` â€” copy of the input
   378	  config the task-store-server reads at boot via Compose `configs:`.
   379	- Stdout: a short "next steps" message â€” `docker compose up -d
   380	  --wait`. (**`up -d`, not `restart`** â€” `restart` does not pick
   381	  up changes to `command:`, env files, or `configs:`. `up -d`
   382	  detects config drift and recreates affected services. See
   383	  https://docs.docker.com/reference/cli/docker/compose/up/.)
   384	
   385	**Step ordering** (one-shot, synchronous, no chicken-and-egg):
   386	
   387	1. Generate / preserve secrets. Write a partial `.env` with
   388	   everything except `EDEN_BASE_COMMIT_SHA`.
   389	2. Copy the input config to `reference/compose/experiment-config.yaml`.
   390	3. `docker compose --env-file .env run --rm eden-repo-init`,
   391	   capture stdout, parse the seed SHA.
   392	4. Append `EDEN_BASE_COMMIT_SHA=<sha>` to `.env`.
   393	5. Print next-steps message.
   394	
   395	If step 3 fails (e.g., the image isn't built yet), the script
   396	errors clearly with the suggestion to run `docker compose
   397	--env-file .env build eden-repo-init` first.
   398	
   399	### F. Compose dependency graph
   400	
   401	Final shape (post-setup-experiment):
   402	
   403	```
   404	postgres          â†’ healthy (10a)
   405	gitea             â†’ healthy (10a, idle this chunk)
   406	blob-init         â†’ exited 0 (10a)
   407	eden-repo-init    â†’ exited 0 (new; profile=setup, NOT in `compose up`)
   408	task-store-server â†’ healthy [depends_on: postgres]
   409	orchestrator      â†’ running [depends_on: task-store-server]
   410	planner-host      â†’ running [depends_on: task-store-server]
   411	implementer-host  â†’ running [depends_on: task-store-server]
   412	evaluator-host    â†’ running [depends_on: task-store-server]
   413	web-ui            â†’ healthy [depends_on: task-store-server]
   414	```
   415	
   416	`eden-repo-init` is invoked once by setup-experiment via
   417	`compose run --rm` *before* `compose up`; the bare-repo volume is
   418	already seeded by the time `compose up` starts the long-running
   419	services, so no `compose up`-time dependency on `eden-repo-init` is
   420	needed.
   421	
   422	Worker hosts and orchestrator are long-running clients without HTTP
   423	healthchecks; `compose up --wait` waits on `service_healthy` for
   424	healthcheck-declaring services and `service_started` for the
   425	others. Acceptable for this chunk.
