    27	## Roadmap delta
    28	
    29	The roadmap's wording for 10b/10c was written ahead of detail; this
    30	chunk amends it explicitly. The amendments below should be reflected
    31	in `docs/roadmap.md` as part of the chunk's diff so the source of
    32	truth doesn't drift.
    33	
    34	| Roadmap text (current) | This chunk does | Why the change |
    35	|---|---|---|
    36	| "10b â€” Each reference service dockerized with its own image." | One shared `eden-reference:dev` image, services selected by Compose `command:`. | The seven services share most deps (FastAPI, uvicorn, eden-contracts, eden-storage, eden-wire, eden-service-common). N images means either replicating the workspace into each (greater total image bytes than one) or a multi-stage tower whose complexity outweighs the benefit. Phase 13 (k8s, Helm) is when "one image per service with its own minimal closure" becomes valuable; not now. |
    37	| "10c â€” builds experiment-specific image" | **Deferred to 10d.** | The scripted workers don't need an experiment-specific image. The LLM implementer (10d) does, since its sandbox runs the experiment's `implement_command`. Pinning the work to the chunk that *uses* it. |
    38	| "10c â€” registers with the control plane" | **Deferred to Phase 12.** | No control plane exists yet. "Registration" reduces to "generate the right env file," which is what setup-experiment does. |
    39	| (Implicit) workers integrate with Gitea as the bare-repo remote | **Deferred to a follow-up sub-chunk after 10d.** | Workers currently use local bare repos via `eden_git.GitRepo` (subprocess `git`). HTTPS push/pull against Gitea requires either remote-aware refactoring of `GitRepo` or per-worker local-clone+sync logic â€” a substantial body of work, not what 10b/10c is asking for. Same posture 10a took toward the blob volume (infrastructure exists; consumer arrives later). |
    40	
    41	The roadmap update commits alongside this chunk's code so future
    42	readers see the amendment.
    43	
    44	## Critical scope clarifications
    45	
    46	Re-stating, with the deltas above accounted for, the four 10c
    47	sub-jobs:
    48	
    49	| 10c sub-job | Disposition |
    50	|---|---|
    51	| Initialize the bare git repo + seed it | **In scope.** Repo lives in a Compose-shared volume `eden-bare-repo`; setup-experiment runs a one-shot `docker compose run --rm eden-repo-init` that seeds the volume and prints the seed SHA. |
    52	| Write per-service sub-configs | **In scope.** The script emits a generated `.env` Compose reads; service `command:` entries thread the right flags. |
    53	| Build experiment-specific image | **Deferred to 10d** (see Roadmap delta above). |
    54	| Register with the control plane | **Deferred to Phase 12** (see Roadmap delta above). |
    55	
    56	**Gitea stays idle this chunk** (see Roadmap delta). Document the
    57	smell explicitly in `reference/compose/README.md` so a reader doesn't
    58	wonder why Gitea is running.
    59	
    60	**`PostgresStore` is in scope.** 10a's chunk note explicitly reserved
    61	Postgres for "`PostgresStore` consumption in 10b". A new
    62	`reference/packages/eden-storage/src/eden_storage/postgres.py` adds a
    63	third backend that satisfies the same `Store` Protocol as
    64	`InMemoryStore` and `SqliteStore`, sharing the transition logic in
    65	`_base.py`. Test parametrization runs the same conformance scenarios
    66	against all three backends. CI gains a test job that brings up a
    67	disposable Postgres container for the parametrized backend tests.
    68	
    69	## What gets created/changed
    70	
    71	### A. `eden-storage` â€” `PostgresStore`
    72	
    73	**New module:** [`reference/packages/eden-storage/src/eden_storage/postgres.py`](../../reference/packages/eden-storage/src/eden_storage/postgres.py)
    74	
    75	**Design:**
    76	
    77	- Backed by [`psycopg[binary]>=3.2`](https://www.psycopg.org/psycopg3/) â€” pure
    78	  Python with prebuilt binaries; no system libpq dependency. Pin to
    79	  `>=3.2,<4`.
    80	- Single connection per `PostgresStore` instance (matches the
    81	  single-process reference pattern; chapter 8 Â§1.2 atomicity needs
    82	  ordered locking, which is simplest with one connection serialized
    83	  by `_lock`). Pooling is a Phase 12 concern when multiple orchestrator
    84	  replicas appear.
    85	- `BEGIN ISOLATION LEVEL SERIALIZABLE` per public op, mirroring
    86	  `SqliteStore`'s `BEGIN IMMEDIATE`. Serializable is the strongest
    87	  isolation Postgres provides; it's the right starting default for
    88	  "make this work; tune later."
    89	- Schema mirrors `_schema.py`'s SQLite version 1 with type
    90	  substitutions:
    91	  - `TEXT` â†’ `text`
    92	  - `AUTOINCREMENT` â†’ `BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY`
    93	  - `data TEXT` â†’ `data jsonb` (lets us index by `data->>'â€¦'`
    94	    later if needed; the SqliteStore writes the same JSON shape, so
    95	    semantically identical)
    96	  - `event(seq â€¦ AUTOINCREMENT)` â†’ `event(seq BIGINT GENERATED
    97	    ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY)`
    98	- `ensure_schema(conn)` lives in a new `_postgres_schema.py` so the
    99	  SqliteStore's `_schema.py` stays SQLite-specific. Migrations table
   100	  is `schema_version(version int primary key)` â€” same shape as
   101	  SQLite.
   102	- `experiment_id` and `metrics_schema` reopen-validation matches
   103	  SqliteStore exactly (chapter 8 Â§4.2).
   104	- The `event_id` resumption logic â€” re-resuming the per-process
   105	  counter from `MAX(seq)` on reopen â€” ports verbatim.
   106	
   107	**Public API:**
   108	
   109	```python
   110	class PostgresStore(_StoreBase):
   111	    def __init__(
   112	        self,
   113	        experiment_id: str,
   114	        dsn: str,                    # postgresql://â€¦ libpq URL
   115	        *,
   116	        metrics_schema: MetricsSchema | None = None,
   117	        now: Callable[[], datetime] | None = None,
   118	        event_id_factory: Callable[[], str] | None = None,
   119	        token_factory: Callable[[], str] | None = None,
   120	    ) -> None: ...
   121	    def close(self) -> None: ...
   122	```
   123	
   124	**Tests:** [`reference/packages/eden-storage/tests/test_postgres_store.py`](../../reference/packages/eden-storage/tests/test_postgres_store.py).
   125	The existing parametrized conformance scenarios (`test_store_*`) gain
   126	a third backend factory keyed on a new `EDEN_TEST_POSTGRES_DSN`
   127	environment variable; if unset, the parametrization skips the
   128	postgres rows. (Same pattern Python projects use for opt-in
   129	integration tests.) CI sets the env var so coverage is enforced
   130	there.
   131	
   132	**`task-store-server` integration:** [`reference/services/task-store-server/src/eden_task_store_server/app.py`](../../reference/services/task-store-server/src/eden_task_store_server/app.py)'s
   133	`build_store(db_path, â€¦)` becomes `build_store(store_url, â€¦)`. The
   134	URL scheme dispatches:
   135	
   136	- `:memory:` â†’ `InMemoryStore`
   137	- `sqlite:///<path>` (or bare `<path>`, for compatibility) â†’
   138	  `SqliteStore`
   139	- `postgresql://â€¦` â†’ `PostgresStore`
   140	
   141	CLI flag rename: `--db-path` â†’ `--store-url`. The old `--db-path`
   142	flag stays as a deprecated alias for one phase to avoid churn â€”
   143	emits a deprecation warning, mapped to `sqlite:///<value>` when the
   144	value isn't `:memory:`. (We can drop it entirely in 10d; nothing in
   145	the production tree uses it.)
   146	
   147	### B. Service Dockerfiles
   148	
   149	**Image strategy: one shared image** containing the whole uv
   150	workspace. Per-service `command:` in `compose.yaml` selects which
   151	module runs.
   152	
   153	**Why one image, not seven:** the seven services share most
   154	dependencies (FastAPI, uvicorn, eden-contracts, eden-storage,
   155	eden-wire, eden-service-common). Building seven images requires
   156	either replicating the whole workspace into each (bigger total
   157	storage than one image) or a multi-stage trick whose complexity
   158	outweighs the benefit. One shared image is what every reference
   159	microservices repo I've worked on does; we get back to the
   160	seven-image story in Phase 13 when each service ships its own Helm
   161	chart with its own minimal image.
   162	
   163	**File:** [`reference/compose/Dockerfile`](../../reference/compose/Dockerfile)
   164	
   165	```dockerfile
   166	# syntax=docker/dockerfile:1.7
   167	ARG PYTHON_VERSION=3.12.7
   168	ARG UV_VERSION=0.5.4
   169	
   170	FROM python:${PYTHON_VERSION}-slim-bookworm AS base
   171	ENV PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1 \
   172	    PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 \
   173	    PIP_DISABLE_PIP_VERSION_CHECK=1
   174	# git is required by eden_git's subprocess wrapper (orchestrator,
   175	# implementer, integrator, web-ui).
   176	RUN apt-get update \
   177	    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends git ca-certificates curl \
   178	    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
   179	RUN useradd --uid 1000 --create-home --shell /bin/bash eden
   180	
   181	FROM base AS builder
   182	ARG UV_VERSION
   183	RUN pip install --no-cache-dir uv==${UV_VERSION}
   184	WORKDIR /app
   185	# Copy the workspace layout first (pyproject + per-member pyproject)
   186	# so dependency layers cache before source.
   187	COPY pyproject.toml uv.lock ./
   188	COPY reference/packages/eden-contracts/pyproject.toml reference/packages/eden-contracts/pyproject.toml
   189	COPY reference/packages/eden-dispatch/pyproject.toml reference/packages/eden-dispatch/pyproject.toml
   190	COPY reference/packages/eden-git/pyproject.toml      reference/packages/eden-git/pyproject.toml
   191	COPY reference/packages/eden-storage/pyproject.toml  reference/packages/eden-storage/pyproject.toml
   192	COPY reference/packages/eden-wire/pyproject.toml     reference/packages/eden-wire/pyproject.toml
   193	COPY reference/services/_common/pyproject.toml          reference/services/_common/pyproject.toml
   194	COPY reference/services/task-store-server/pyproject.toml reference/services/task-store-server/pyproject.toml
   195	COPY reference/services/orchestrator/pyproject.toml      reference/services/orchestrator/pyproject.toml
   196	COPY reference/services/planner/pyproject.toml           reference/services/planner/pyproject.toml
   197	COPY reference/services/implementer/pyproject.toml       reference/services/implementer/pyproject.toml
   198	COPY reference/services/evaluator/pyproject.toml         reference/services/evaluator/pyproject.toml
   199	COPY reference/services/web-ui/pyproject.toml            reference/services/web-ui/pyproject.toml
   200	# README files referenced from per-member pyproject (hatchling needs them).
   201	COPY reference/packages reference/packages
   202	COPY reference/services reference/services
   203	# `--all-packages` installs every workspace member; without it the
   204	# eden-* packages would be skipped because the root `pyproject.toml`
   205	# is non-installable (`tool.uv.package = false`) and the workspace
   206	# members are pulled in only via the `dev` group, which `--no-dev`
   207	# excludes. Verified empirically: `uv sync --frozen --no-dev` against
   208	# this workspace removes every eden-* package from the venv.
   209	RUN uv sync --frozen --no-dev --all-packages
   210	
   211	FROM base AS runtime
   212	WORKDIR /app
   213	COPY --from=builder /app /app
   214	# Make uv-installed venv binaries discoverable.
   215	ENV PATH="/app/.venv/bin:${PATH}"
   216	USER eden
   217	# No ENTRYPOINT â€” compose.yaml's `command:` selects the service
   218	# module.
   219	```
   220	
   221	**Build context:** the **repo root** (so the workspace files are
   222	reachable). compose.yaml uses `context: ..` and
   223	`dockerfile: reference/compose/Dockerfile`.
   224	
   225	**`.dockerignore`** (new file at repo root) excludes `.git`,
   226	`.venv`, `node_modules`, `__pycache__`, `*.egg-info`,
   227	`.pytest_cache`, `.ruff_cache`, `dist`, `build`, `htmlcov`. Without
   228	this, `uv sync --frozen` re-downloads every dep on each build
   229	because the hash of the build context changes whenever `git`
   230	internal files do.
   231	
   232	### C. Compose service entries
   233	
   234	[`reference/compose/compose.yaml`](../../reference/compose/compose.yaml) gains six service entries
   235	(below). Each service:
   236	
   237	1. `build:` references the shared image.
   238	2. `depends_on:` waits for `postgres` (healthy) for those that talk
   239	   to the task-store-server, which itself depends on postgres.
   240	3. `command:` selects the module + threads the right flags from
   241	   `${VAR}` substitutions, so setup-experiment generating a `.env`
   242	   is the one source of dynamic config.
   243	4. Bare-repo-touching services mount the named volume `eden-bare-repo`.
   244	
   245	**Service config matrix.** Each row spells out every required flag,
   246	where the flag's value comes from, and what mounts the service
   247	needs.
   248	
   249	| Service | `command:` flags | Source of each value | Mounts | `depends_on` (healthy) | Healthcheck | Host port |
   250	|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
   251	| `task-store-server` | `--store-url $EDEN_STORE_URL`, `--experiment-id $EDEN_EXPERIMENT_ID`, `--experiment-config /etc/eden/experiment-config.yaml`, `--shared-token $EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN`, `--host 0.0.0.0`, `--port 8080`, `--log-level info` | env from `.env` (setup-experiment); experiment-config from Compose `configs:` (setup-experiment) | `eden-experiment-config` (configs), no volumes | `postgres` | `curl -fsS http://localhost:8080/v0/experiments/$EDEN_EXPERIMENT_ID/events -H "Authorization: Bearer $EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN" -H "X-Eden-Experiment-Id: $EDEN_EXPERIMENT_ID"` | none (internal) |
   252	| `orchestrator` | `--task-store-url http://task-store-server:8080`, `--experiment-id $EDEN_EXPERIMENT_ID`, `--shared-token $EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN`, `--repo-path /var/lib/eden/repo`, `--plan-tasks $EDEN_PLAN_TASKS`, `--log-level info` | env + Compose service DNS | `eden-bare-repo` at `/var/lib/eden/repo` | `task-store-server` | none (long-running client) | none |
   253	| `planner-host` | `--task-store-url http://task-store-server:8080`, `--experiment-id $EDEN_EXPERIMENT_ID`, `--shared-token $EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN`, `--worker-id planner-1`, `--base-commit-sha $EDEN_BASE_COMMIT_SHA`, `--log-level info` | env (worker-id is a static literal in compose.yaml; override via env if multiple replicas needed later) | none | `task-store-server` | none | none |
   254	| `implementer-host` | `--task-store-url http://task-store-server:8080`, `--experiment-id $EDEN_EXPERIMENT_ID`, `--shared-token $EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN`, `--worker-id implementer-1`, `--repo-path /var/lib/eden/repo`, `--log-level info` | env | `eden-bare-repo` at `/var/lib/eden/repo` | `task-store-server` | none | none |
   255	| `evaluator-host` | `--task-store-url http://task-store-server:8080`, `--experiment-id $EDEN_EXPERIMENT_ID`, `--shared-token $EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN`, `--worker-id evaluator-1`, `--experiment-config /etc/eden/experiment-config.yaml`, `--log-level info` | env + configs | `eden-experiment-config` (configs) | `task-store-server` | none | none |
   256	| `web-ui` | `--task-store-url http://task-store-server:8080`, `--experiment-id $EDEN_EXPERIMENT_ID`, `--shared-token $EDEN_SHARED_TOKEN`, `--experiment-config /etc/eden/experiment-config.yaml`, `--session-secret $EDEN_SESSION_SECRET`, `--artifacts-dir /var/lib/eden/artifacts`, `--repo-path /var/lib/eden/repo`, `--worker-id web-ui-1`, `--host 0.0.0.0`, `--port 8090`, `--log-level info` | env + configs | `eden-experiment-config` (configs); `eden-artifacts-data` at `/var/lib/eden/artifacts`; `eden-bare-repo` at `/var/lib/eden/repo` (read-only is enough for the admin work-refs page) | `task-store-server` | `curl -fsS http://localhost:8090/healthz` (new endpoint added in this chunk) | `${WEB_UI_HOST_PORT:-8090}:8090` |
   257	| `eden-repo-init` (profile: setup) | `python -m eden_service_common.repo_init --repo-path /var/lib/eden/repo` | n/a â€” invoked by setup-experiment via `compose run --rm` | `eden-bare-repo` at `/var/lib/eden/repo` | none | n/a (one-shot) | n/a |
   258	
   259	**New named volumes**: `eden-bare-repo` (replaces the host-path repo
   260	the existing CLIs assume) and `eden-artifacts-data` (web-ui's

